# CohGenT Administrator Guide (DRAFT)

## Introduction

### Purpose of this Guide

Audience: CDC application administrators, program “power users,” and IT operations staff.
Scope: Configuration, governance, support, and operations of CohGenT. (Note: day‑to‑day scenario creation lives in the User Guide.)

### What CohGenT Does 

Generates synthetic FHIR‑conformant patient records for public health scenarios.
Supports USCDI‑aligned data elements.
Outputs JSON or NDJSON for downstream testing and analytics.
Runs only in CDC’s private environment; no real patient data is processed.

## Roles, Permissions, and Access Management
### Role Definitions:
* System Administrator
  * Manages application configuration, integrations, releases. 
  * Can access all scenarios, logs, and system settings.
* Application Administrator / Program Admin
  * Manages scenarios, reusable configurations, and output destinations.
  * Can create/modify existing back-end features (e.g., demographics, clinincal data).
* Standard User
  * Can create and run cohorts using available scenarios and templates.
  * Limited ability to change global settings.

